WEBVTT

00:00.767 --> 00:05.794
1.4 million people in Sao Paulo proudly sporting the colors of Brazil.

00:06.198 --> 00:10.173
Patriotic crowds have swapped their football chants for a political message:

00:10.528 --> 00:11.783
Get Dilma out.

00:13.002 --> 00:15.491
I came to protest against corruption in Brazil.

00:16.479 --> 00:20.387
The only way to solve this is to take to the streets and show them what we want.

00:22.379 --> 00:24.579
An equal turnout in Rio de Janeiro,..

00:24.921 --> 00:27.595
...further testing the president's political survival skills...

00:27.819 --> 00:29.937
...in Latin America's largest economy.

00:30.405 --> 00:33.537
Dilma Rousseff's approval ratings have sunk to a record low...

00:33.840 --> 00:37.815
...as her Worker's Party faces a probe into massive bribes and embezzlement,...

00:37.985 --> 00:40.288
...involving state oil company Petrobras.

